86/1.text_en:
Section 86/1. The provisions prescribing the acquisition of land by an alien by virtue of the provisions of a treaty under the first paragraph of Section 86 shall not apply to an alien who brings in foreign currency for investment in the amount of not less than forty million Baht as prescribed in the Ministerial Regulation, provided that:
(1) The acquisition of land shall be for the purpose of residential use only;
(2) The land shall not exceed one rai;
(3) The land shall be located within the area designated for residential purposes under the Town Planning Act;
(4) The Minister must give approval.
If the alien who has acquired land under this Section fails to comply with the conditions prescribed in the Ministerial Regulation or does not use the land for residential purposes within two years from the date of registration of the acquisition, or uses the land for purposes other than residential, the provisions of Section 94 shall apply mutatis mutandis.

87.text_en:
Section 87. Unless subject to the provisions of Section 86, aliens may acquire land upon the following conditions:
(1) For carrying on business not prohibited by law, the land may be acquired but shall not exceed the areas prescribed in the Ministerial Regulation;
(2) For residential purposes of each alien family, the area shall not exceed one rai;
(3) For charitable or public benefit purposes, the area shall not exceed one half rai;
(4) For the purpose of a cemetery, the area shall not exceed one half rai per family.

97.text_en:
Section 97. The following juristic persons shall be deemed to be aliens for the purpose of this Chapter:
(1) A limited company or a public limited company of which the shares representing more than forty-nine percent of the total shares are held by aliens or in which more than half of the shareholders are aliens, even though such aliens hold less than half of the total shares;
(2) A registered ordinary partnership or a limited partnership of which the capital contributed by aliens constitutes more than forty-nine percent of the total capital;
(3) Societies, cooperatives, incorporated bodies or other organizations registered in Thailand of which the members or participants constituting more than half of the total members are aliens.
